-- At Least 50 Dead After Two Trains Collide in West Bengal, Press Trust Says
-- Saikat Chatterjee
-- 2010-07-19T01:46:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/at-least-50-dead-after-two-trains-collide-in-west-bengal-press-trust-says.html

          
          
             A train crash in eastern India has
killed at least 50 people, Press Trust of India reported, citing
an official it didn’t identify.  
 The Uttarbanga Express train collided with the stationary
Vananchal Express at Sainthia railway station in West Bengal
state, the news agency said. At least 15 bodies have been
recovered, the report said, citing people it didn’t identify at
a local hospital. The accident occurred at 1:54 a.m. local time,
the report said.  
